{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":769,"text":"I want you guys to imagine \nthat you're a soldier"},{"time":3327,"text":"running through the battlefield."},{"time":5228,"text":"Now, you're shot in the leg with a bullet,"},{"time":7444,"text":"which severs your femoral artery."},{"time":9671,"text":"Now, this bleed is extremely traumatic"},{"time":11797,"text":"and can kill you in less \nthan three minutes."},{"time":14532,"text":"Unfortunately, by the time that a medic"},{"time":16600,"text":"actually gets to you,"},{"time":18276,"text":"what the medic has on his or her belt"},{"time":20527,"text":"can take five minutes or more,"},{"time":22787,"text":"with the application of pressure,\nto stop that type of bleed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25951,"text":"Now, this problem is \nnot only a huge problem"},{"time":28204,"text":"for the military, but it's \nalso a huge problem"},{"time":30893,"text":"that's epidemic throughout \nthe entire medical field,"},{"time":33875,"text":"which is how do we actually look at wounds"},{"time":36506,"text":"and how do we stop them quickly"},{"time":38307,"text":"in a way that can work with the body?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40668,"text":"So now, what I've been working\non for the last four years"},{"time":43481,"text":"is to develop smart biomaterials,"},{"time":46476,"text":"which are actually materials that will work"},{"time":48453,"text":"with the body, helping it to heal"},{"time":50635,"text":"and helping it to allow the \nwounds to heal normally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54995,"text":"So now, before we do this, we \nhave to take a much closer look"},{"time":58585,"text":"at actually how does the body work."},{"time":60743,"text":"So now, everybody here knows"},{"time":62133,"text":"that the body is made up of cells."},{"time":64230,"text":"So the cell is the most basic unit of life."},{"time":66947,"text":"But not many people know what else."},{"time":69411,"text":"But it actually turns out that your cells"},{"time":71942,"text":"sit in this mesh of complicated fibers,"},{"time":74686,"text":"proteins and sugars"},{"time":76319,"text":"known as the extracellular matrix."},{"time":78331,"text":"So now, the ECM"},{"time":80160,"text":"is actually this mesh that \nholds the cells in place,"},{"time":83190,"text":"provides structure for your tissues,"},{"time":85030,"text":"but it also gives the cells a home."},{"time":87476,"text":"It allows them to feel what they're doing,"},{"time":89603,"text":"where they are, and tells them"},{"time":91188,"text":"how to act and how to behave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93528,"text":"And it actually turns out that \nthe extracellular matrix"},{"time":96460,"text":"is different from every \nsingle part of the body."},{"time":99423,"text":"So the ECM in my skin"},{"time":100840,"text":"is different than the ECM in my liver,"},{"time":102955,"text":"and the ECM in different \nparts of the same organ"},{"time":105733,"text":"actually vary, so it's very difficult"},{"time":107941,"text":"to be able to have a product"},{"time":109718,"text":"that will react to the \nlocal extracellular matrix,"},{"time":112125,"text":"which is exactly what we're trying to do."},{"time":114218,"text":"So now, for example, \nthink of the rainforest."},{"time":116940,"text":"You have the canopy, \nyou have the understory,"},{"time":119325,"text":"and you have the forest floor."},{"time":120900,"text":"Now, all of these parts of the forest"},{"time":122685,"text":"are made up of different plants,"},{"time":124451,"text":"and different animals call them home."},{"time":126869,"text":"So just like that, the extracellular matrix"},{"time":129180,"text":"is incredibly diverse in three dimensions."},{"time":131972,"text":"On top of that, the extracellular matrix"},{"time":134889,"text":"is responsible for all wound healing,"},{"time":137420,"text":"so if you imagine cutting the body,"},{"time":139175,"text":"you actually have to rebuild"},{"time":141200,"text":"this very complex ECM"},{"time":143157,"text":"in order to get it to form again,"},{"time":145200,"text":"and a scar, in fact, is actually"},{"time":146779,"text":"poorly formed extracellular matrix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150233,"text":"So now, behind me is an animation"},{"time":152291,"text":"of the extracellular matrix."},{"time":153899,"text":"So as you see, your cells sit \nin this complicated mesh"},{"time":156555,"text":"and as you move throughout the tissue,"},{"time":159187,"text":"the extracellular matrix changes."},{"time":161268,"text":"So now every other piece \nof technology on the market"},{"time":164075,"text":"can only manage a two-\ndimensional approximation"},{"time":167151,"text":"of the extracellular matrix,"},{"time":168906,"text":"which means that it doesn't fit in"},{"time":170694,"text":"with the tissue itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172460,"text":"So when I was a freshman at NYU,"},{"time":174260,"text":"what I discovered was \nyou could actually take"},{"time":176464,"text":"small pieces of plant-derived polymers"},{"time":178985,"text":"and reassemble them onto the wound."},{"time":181639,"text":"So if you have a bleeding \nwound like the one behind me,"},{"time":184297,"text":"you can actually put \nour material onto this,"},{"time":186870,"text":"and just like Lego blocks,"},{"time":188810,"text":"it'll reassemble into the local tissue."},{"time":190993,"text":"So that means if you put it onto liver,"},{"time":192859,"text":"it turns into something \nthat looks like liver,"},{"time":194610,"text":"and if you put it onto skin,"},{"time":196133,"text":"it turns into something \nthat looks just like skin."},{"time":198236,"text":"So when you put the gel on,"},{"time":199616,"text":"it actually reassembles \ninto this local tissue."},{"time":202927,"text":"So now, this has a whole \nbunch of applications,"},{"time":206533,"text":"but basically the idea is,\nwherever you put this product,"},{"time":209485,"text":"you're able to reassemble \ninto it immediately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212320,"text":"Now, this is a simulated arterial bleed —"},{"time":214681,"text":"blood warning —"},{"time":216040,"text":"at twice human artery pressure."},{"time":217840,"text":"So now, this type of bleed \nis incredibly traumatic,"},{"time":220273,"text":"and like I said before, \nwould actually take"},{"time":222500,"text":"five minutes or more with pressure"},{"time":224356,"text":"to be able to stop."},{"time":225728,"text":"Now, in the time that it takes\nme to introduce the bleed itself,"},{"time":228749,"text":"our material is able to stop that bleed,"},{"time":230878,"text":"and it's because it actually \ngoes on and works"},{"time":233154,"text":"with the body to heal,"},{"time":234886,"text":"so it reassembles into this piece of meat,"},{"time":237258,"text":"and then the blood actually recognizes"},{"time":240138,"text":"that that's happening, \nand produces fibrin,"},{"time":242725,"text":"producing a very fast clot in less than 10 seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246470,"text":"So now this technology — Thank you."},{"time":248349,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256606,"text":"So now this technology, by January,\nwill be in the hands of veterinarians,"},{"time":260188,"text":"and we're working very diligently to \ntry to get it into the hands of doctors,"},{"time":263765,"text":"hopefully within the next year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265530,"text":"But really, once again, I \nwant you guys to imagine"},{"time":268137,"text":"that you are a soldier running \nthrough a battlefield."},{"time":270160,"text":"Now, you get hit in the leg with a bullet,"},{"time":271927,"text":"and instead of bleeding \nout in three minutes,"},{"time":275260,"text":"you pull a small pack \nof gel out of your belt,"},{"time":277248,"text":"and with the press of a button,"},{"time":278575,"text":"you're able to stop your own bleed"},{"time":279984,"text":"and you're on your way to recovery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281893,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283783,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}